  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly chop (keep the colours separate!)</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690280582468-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690280582468-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690280582468-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690280582468-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690280582468-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> and <strong>chopped yellow pepper </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with the<strong> onion wedges</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> (save the rest for later!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20 min – these are your<strong> roasted veggies</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690280612727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690280612727-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690280612727-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690280612727-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690280612727-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are roasting, add the <strong>chopped red pepper</strong> to a separate, <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray, then scrunch the sides up to create a parcel </p><p>Add the <strong>peeled garlic</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to the parcel and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the pepper is softened and golden – this is your <strong>roasted pepper mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
